                q: `When is dropping to native SQL justified?`,
                a: `Window functions, CTEs/recursive queries, vendor features (ON CONFLICT/MERGE), heavy reporting aggregations, and hot paths needing exact plan control — mapped to DTOs, with cache eviction for native writes.`
