                a: `~40 writes/s (peak ~120/s), ~4k reads/s (peak ~12k/s), ~3 TB over 5 years (6B rows × ~500 B). Conclusion to state: this is small-data and read-hot, so the design centers on cache + replicas, not sharding.`
